.TH "acpi_set_modalias" 9 "acpi_set_modalias" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
acpi_set_modalias \- Set modalias using "compatible" property or supplied ID
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" acpi_set_modalias
.BI "(struct acpi_device *adev "  ","
.BI "const char *default_id "  ","
.BI "char *modalias "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adev" 12
ACPI device object to match
.IP "default_id" 12
ID string to use as default if no compatible string found
.IP "modalias" 12
Pointer to buffer that modalias value will be copied into
.IP "len" 12
Length of modalias buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a counterpart of \fBof_modalias_node\fP for struct acpi_device objects.
If there is a compatible string for \fIadev\fP, it will be copied to \fImodalias\fP
with the vendor prefix stripped; otherwise, \fIdefault_id\fP will be used.
